# Copy this file to ".env" and paste your real keys after the "=".
# Never commit the real .env — it is git-ignored for you.
#
# Mason's DEFAULT chat brain (Claude on your Claude Code subscription) needs NO key —
# so the out-of-the-box setup needs NOTHING in this file. (The composition ENGINE is
# pure, deterministic code — it calls no LLM at all.)

# --- LLM brain (chat + memory distill only) ----------------------------------
# DEFAULT (MASON_LLM unset) = Claude on your Claude Code SUBSCRIPTION via the Agent
# SDK. No key required. Do NOT set ANTHROPIC_API_KEY — it is NOT needed for the
# default, and if set it makes the SDK bill the pay-per-token API instead of your
# subscription (llm.py warns you if it sees it).
#
# Switch brains with the MASON_LLM env var (one switch, see llm.py):
#   MASON_LLM=gemini    -> needs GEMINI_API_KEY below
#   MASON_LLM=deepseek  -> needs DEEPSEEK_API_KEY below

# Google Gemini (free) — only for MASON_LLM=gemini (and the weak-model persona test).
# Free key: https://aistudio.google.com -> "Get API key".
# GEMINI_API_KEY=your-free-gemini-api-key-here

# DeepSeek — only for MASON_LLM=deepseek.
# Key: https://platform.deepseek.com -> API keys.
# DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=your-deepseek-api-key-here

# --- Build/CI escape hatch ---------------------------------------------------
# MASON_SKIP_RENDER=1 skips the actual MP4 renders (HTML build + auto-gate still run)
# for fast offline pipeline/CI checks. Leave UNSET for real composition.
# MASON_SKIP_RENDER=1
